# P2P File Drop

[![Go](https://img.shields.io/badge/Go-1.22-blue)]()
[![React](https://img.shields.io/badge/React-18-61dafb)]()
[![WebRTC](https://img.shields.io/badge/WebRTC-P2P-green)]()
[![Docker](https://img.shields.io/badge/Docker-ready-2496ed)]()
[![Wails](https://img.shields.io/badge/Wails-desktop-orange)]()

Local LAN file sharing app with real peer-to-peer transfer over WebRTC.

---

## 🎥 Demo

> Add screenshots or GIFs here (UI, transfer, progress bar)

---

## 🚀 Features

* Direct P2P transfer (WebRTC DataChannel)
* LAN device discovery (UDP)
* WebSocket signaling (Go)
* File upload / download
* Transfer progress bar
* Desktop app (Wails)

---

## 🧱 Architecture

Client (React)
↓
WebSocket (Signaling)
↓
WebRTC (P2P DataChannel)
↓
Client (Peer)

---

## 🖥 Run

### Backend

```bash
cd сmd/server
go run main.go
```

### Frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open:

```
http://localhost:5173
```

---

## 🧪 Test P2P

1. Open 2 tabs
2. Upload file
3. Select peer
4. Send

---

## 🐳 Docker

```bash
docker build -t p2p-file-drop .
docker run -p 9999:9999 p2p-file-drop
```

---

## 🖥 Desktop (Wails)

```bash
wails dev
```

Build:

```bash
wails build
```

---

## 📌 Notes

* Optimized for LAN usage
* TURN fallback enabled
* No auth (intentionally simple UX)

---

## 📈 Future

* Multi-file transfer
* Speed indicator
* Resume transfer
* Mobile UI

